FBIS4-49786 "drchi091_f_94003" FBIS-CHI-94-091 Daily Report 10 May 1994 Near East & South Asia More on Evacuation More on Evacuation OW1005115694 Beijing XINHUA in English 1139 GMT 10 May 94 OW1005115694 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Beijing, May 10 (XINHUA) -- All the Chinese in Yemen are safe and sound and will leave the country very soon, a spokesman for the Chinese Foreign Ministry said here today. In response to a question whether the Chinese in Yemen have been evacuated as recently serious armed conflicts have taken place in Yemen, the spokesman said the Chinese Government is very concerned about the safety of the Chinese diplomats, engineers and workers in Yemen, and has instructed departments concerned to arrange for their evacuation. On May 5, armed conflicts occurred between the south and north sides of Yemen, with the fighting mainly concentrated in south part of the country. Up to now, he said, all the Chinese in Yemen are safe and sound. He said that most of the Chinese personnel working in the south have already been evacuated to Djibouti by sea. "The rest will leave very soon", he added. The spokesman said that the evacuation "is conducted in a smooth fashion".
